title: Paul Cezanne Bathers (Les Grandes Baigneuses) Matted Notecard
description:
Print developed from Paul Cezanne’s Bathers (Les Grandes Baigneuses), About 1894-1905.

Around 200 of Cezanne’s works depict male and female nude bathers, either singly or in groups, in a landscape. This large painting is one of three pictures of female bathers that Cézanne worked on during the final decade of his life. They represent the culmination of his lifelong investigation of this subject and the climax of his entire career, and were hugely influential on early twentieth-century art
